label: DAD-101
info_overview: One channel dimmer with ability to add different sensors to it.
info_inclusion:
1. Put controller in inclusion mode.
  2. Power on device. It should be added automatically (using NWI).
  3. If not fast press add/remove button three times.
info_exclusion:
1. Put controller in exclusion mode.
  2. Fast press add/remove button three times.

category_description: Any device attached to the wall that controls a binary status of something, for ex. a light switch

parameters.label: Dimming speed
parameters.overview: Dimming speed in seconds (0 - instantly) WARNING - 0 does not work correctly, it leaves 11-15V AC on the terminals. Use 1 instead!

options.label: Disable
options.overview: WARNING - not working correctly with the latest firmware, use Fastest(1) option instead.

parameters.label: Auto Off delay
parameters.description: Delay to turn device OFF after ON command received
parameters.overview: Sets time after which dimmer will turn off after receiving ON command in 1 sec. (0 - disable feature)

parameters.label: All ON/OFF behaviour
parameters.overview:
0 - React on All ON/All OFF

1 - Ignore All ON/All OFF

2 - Ignore All ON/React on All OFF

3 - React on All ON/Ignore All OFF

options.label: ON
options.overview: If lighting sensor DSM-111 is added to dimmer. See parameter 9.

options.label: Use with motion sensor
options.overview: Same as option 1 but also turns on/off device based on motion sensor DSM-111

parameters.label: Smart delay mode
parameters.overview:
DAD-101

0 - implicit smart delay

1 - use smart delay for all devices NOT in Group 1. Also smart delay ignored for controller and button issued commands

2 - use smart delay for all devices IN Group 1. Also smart delay will be used for controller and button issued commands

options.label: Bistable (fixed switch)
options.overview:
Switch ON - S1 is ON

Switch OFF - S1 is OFF

options.label: Bistable (reversed fixed switch)
options.overview:
Switch ON - S1 is OFF

Switch OFF - S1 is ON

options.label: Two monostable switches
options.overview: Both S1 and S2 switches used in this mode. S1 used for ON/Level up, S2 - OFF/Level down

parameters.label: S2 button mode
parameters.overview: Type of button connected to S2 switch

options.label: Bistable (fixed switch button)
options.overview:
Switch ON - S2 is ON

Switch OFF - S2 is OFF

options.label: Bistable (reversed fixed switch)
options.overview:
Switch ON - S2 is OFF

Switch OFF - S2 is ON

parameters.label: Double click to max
parameters.description: Level up to max on double click

parameters.label: Sensor 1 command OFF value
parameters.description: Value to activate OFF command for Sensor 1

commandclass.name: NO_OPERATION
commandclass.label: No Operation - used for PINGing a device.
